706166f-a.title: Brooklyn: Pacific Street - 3rd Avenue
706166f-a.text:
(1)
Pacific Street, north side, between Third and Fourth Aves. In the
background, is shown the upper floors and tower of the Williamsburg Savings
Bank Building.
May 11, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same, showing a more westerly view of No. 1.
May 11, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.

702244f-a.title: Brooklyn: 3rd Avenue - Pacific Street
702244f-a.text:
Third Ave., at the S.W. corner of Pacific Street. In the foreground,
is seen the proposed New York Times Building excavation at the S.E. corner
of Pacific Street. Building concerned is the Swedish Evangelist Church.
January 26, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.

702243f-a.title: Brooklyn: 3rd Avenue - Pacific Street
702243f-a.text:
Third Ave., at and adjoining the S.E. corner of Pacific Street. Also
shown is Pacific Street, south side, from and including Third, to but not
including Fourth Aves. The view shows a frame house at No 6l Third Ave.
May 29, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
